   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>14.8.1885 Freitag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49289">Rigi</placeName>
               <orgName key="49369">Kaltbad</orgName>. August 14. 1885 Friday</p>
            <p>Played with Baby<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="104">Brion, Wilma</persName>
               </note> and read at the music in the morning. Afterwards I walked to the Känzli and
               wrote to young <persName key="7851">Schwabach</persName>
               <note type="reg">Paul</note>. Then I played ball with <persName key="104">Gee</persName>. She laughed a good deal and was very amused. <persName key="103">Mamma</persName> sat writing. After dinner sat with <persName key="104">Gee</persName> down at the music and read the <name type="work" key="28732">Lendemain de la Mort</name>
               <note type="reg">
                  <persName key="81660">Figuier</persName>
               </note>. Also talked with <persName key="1878">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                  </hi> Delfosse</persName> about Auvergne and Auvergnat. He said the country was
               most interesting and the language very soft. After this walked out with <persName key="103">Mamma</persName>. First saw the châlet which seems very nice and has 8
               rooms. Then went on the way to First. We were not very far when we saw dear little
                  <persName key="104">Baby</persName> running after us and <persName key="536">Marie</persName> behind her. As she stood admiring the painting bear with the
               spectacles <persName key="1855">Kuseberg</persName> came up and after long
               marchendeing he bought it for her and gave it her afterwards in the <orgName key="49369">hôtel</orgName>. Unfortunately he walked with us the whole time so
               that we were glad to get home. We had not been home long when <persName key="1876">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">rs</hi>
                  </hi> Langley </persName>came up to see the Alpenglühen from the balcony. Of
               course she stuck till 7.20. At supper she almost had a row with <persName key="1879">old Langley</persName> because she very tactlessly asked <persName key="103">Mamma</persName> to get her half a pound of bonbons at <placeName key="49287">Lucerne</placeName> in the short time she had there. <persName key="1879">Old
                  Langley</persName> got furious and said he had never seen such a tactless woman.
               After dinner sat a little with <persName key="103">Mamma</persName> and <persName key="104">Gee</persName> while they were going to bed, and <persName key="104">Gee</persName> lay a little in <persName key="103">Mammas</persName> bed
               afterwards and I talked to her. She showed me her foot and was very amusing. Bought
               presents for Blümers<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="1163">Auguste</persName> und <persName key="1162">Wilhelm</persName>
               </note> in the afternoon and got <persName key="104">Gee</persName> a Schweizerhaus
               with which she was very pleased. 1525 people died in Spain of cholera.</p>
